<p>I have following jsp:</p>  <pre class="lang-jsp prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;form id="windowForm" name="windowForm" method="post" action="task_update"&gt;     ...     &lt;a href="#place" onclick="JavaScript:saveAndClose(this); return false;"&gt;Save&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/form&gt; ... &lt;script language="JavaScript"&gt;      function saveAndClose(evnt){           ...           window.windowForm.action = "task_update";           window.windowForm.submit();           window.close();      } &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <h2>web.xml</h2>  <pre class="lang-xml prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;servlet-mapping&gt;     &lt;url-pattern&gt;task_update&lt;/url-pattern&gt;     &lt;servlet-name&gt;TaskUpdateServlet&lt;/servlet-name&gt; &lt;/servlet-mapping&gt; </code></pre>  <h2>TaskUpdateServlet.java</h2>  <pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>public void execute(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response)         throws Exception {     // ...      PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();     out.println("&lt;script language='javascript'&gt;document.close();window.close();&lt;/script&gt;");     request.setAttribute("has_token", true);     return; } </code></pre>  <p>After submitting this form it is blank window at Chrome with address: <code>myapp/task_update</code>. At Chrome console I can see <code>Scripts may close only the windows that were opened by it.</code> Also I believe that closing window at jsp function <code>saveAndClose()</code>causes that data doesn't get saved as page is closed before servlet is done (dependes on browser).</p>  <p>I've tried to remove window.close() from jsp and also modified java out.pritln:</p>  <pre><code>var customWindow = window.open('', '_blank', ''); customWindow.close(); </code></pre>  <p>and </p>  <pre><code>open(location, '_self').close(); </code></pre>  <p>with no results</p>